cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing tasks such as relation extraction. Additionally, the use of neural networks and learned representations suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with structured learning, which could place it in the sub-categories of cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
